e dialectic by which sovereignty manages to be both the cause of our vulnerabilization and the phantasmatic tool of its prevention, in Being Vulnerable Arne De Boever explores how today’s experiences of vulnerabilization can be translated into a collective human power that dismantles the form of sovereignty that is producing this state of affairs. Focused on theories, paradigms, and alternative formations of sovereignty, Being Vulnerable reconsiders the tradition of thinking through a political concept in order to approach it anew.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSovereigntyxPolitical aspects. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aAchille Mbembe.  aBonnie Honig.  aCarl Schmitt.  aChantal Mouffe.  aEyal Weizman.  aGiorgio Agamben.  aGregoire Chamayou.  aIsabell Lorey.  aJasbir Puar.  aJudith Butler.  aMichel Foucault.  aSantiago Zabala.  aSovereignty.  aTa-Nehisi Coates.  aWalter Benjamin.  aWendy Brown.  aanarchy.  abiopolitics.  acamp.  acivil war.  ademocracy.  adrone.  aexception.  ahomo vulnerabilis.  aindigeneity.  ainstitution.  aneoliberalism.  aphilosophy.  apolice.  awall.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228016298?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228016298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228016298/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles